# UI/UX Guidelines

## Design Philosophy - Collection-Focused Usability

Inspired by [XIV-Complete](mdc:https:/xiv-complete.com), the FFXI Progress Tracker prioritizes **collection management** and **quick navigation** between different tracking categories. The design emphasizes clean organization, visual progress indicators, and efficient workflows for completionist players.

## Core Design Patterns

### Tab-Based Navigation
- **Primary navigation** via horizontal tabs at the top
- **Progress indicators** in tab labels (e.g., "Jobs 15/22", "Trusts 142/287")
- **Active state** clearly distinguished from inactive tabs
- **Responsive behavior** - stack or scroll on mobile devices
- **Quick switching** between different collection types

### Collection List Layout
- **Vertical list structure** for all collection items
- **Row-based items** with consistent spacing and alignment
- **Expandable/collapsible sections** using accordion pattern
- **Visual state indicators** (completed, in-progress, not started)
- **Hover effects** for interactive feedback

### Search & Filtering System
- **Prominent search bar** at the top of each collection
- **Quick filter buttons** (All, Acquired, Unacquired)
- **Advanced filters** in collapsible panels or dropdowns
- **Real-time filtering** as user types or selects options
- **Clear filter state** with easy reset options

## Component Patterns

### Progress Indicators
- **Circular progress** for completion percentages
- **Progress bars** for skill levels, experience, etc.
- **Badge counters** showing completion ratios (15/22)
- **Color coding** for different progress states
- **Visual hierarchy** to highlight important metrics

### Item Cards/Rows
- **Consistent item layout** across all collections
- **Icon + Name + Progress** as primary information
- **Secondary info** revealed on expansion
- **Status indicators** (checkmarks, progress bars, etc.)
- **Quick actions** available without expansion

### State Management
- **Visual feedback** for all user interactions
- **Loading states** during data operations
- **Error handling** with clear messaging
- **Success confirmations** for updates
- **Undo capabilities** where appropriate

## Responsive Design

### Desktop (1024px+)
- **Full tab navigation** with progress indicators
- **Multi-column layouts** where appropriate
- **Sidebar filters** for advanced filtering
- **Hover states** and keyboard shortcuts
- **Efficient use of screen space**

### Tablet (768px - 1023px)
- **Horizontal scrolling tabs** if needed
- **Touch-friendly targets** (44px minimum)
- **Collapsed filters** in slide-out panels
- **Optimized spacing** for touch interaction

### Mobile (< 768px)
- **Bottom tab navigation** or hamburger menu
- **Single column layout** for all collections
- **Swipe gestures** for navigation
- **Thumb-friendly touch targets**
- **Minimal chrome** to maximize content space

## Accessibility Standards

### Keyboard Navigation
- **Tab order** follows logical flow
- **Enter/Space** for activation
- **Arrow keys** for list navigation
- **Escape** to close modals/filters
- **Focus indicators** clearly visible

### Screen Reader Support
- **Semantic HTML** structure
- **ARIA labels** for complex interactions
- **Progress announcements** for dynamic updates
- **Clear headings** hierarchy
- **Alt text** for all images/icons

### Visual Accessibility
- **Color contrast** minimum 4.5:1 ratio
- **Focus indicators** highly visible
- **No color-only** information
- **Scalable text** up to 200%
- **Reduced motion** preferences respected

## Theme & Visual Design

### Color System
- **Dark theme primary** with light theme option
- **Progress colors**: Green (complete), Blue (in-progress), Gray (not started)
- **Accent colors** for interactive elements
- **Semantic colors** for success, warning, error states
- **Brand colors** that reflect FFXI aesthetic

### Typography
- **Clear hierarchy** with consistent sizing
- **Readable fonts** optimized for data display
- **Monospace** for numerical data when appropriate
- **Line spacing** optimized for scanning lists
- **Font weights** to establish information hierarchy

### Spacing & Layout
- **Consistent spacing scale** (4px, 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px)
- **Grid system** for alignment
- **White space** to prevent cognitive overload
- **Breathing room** around interactive elements
- **Visual grouping** through proximity

## Collection-Specific Patterns

### Jobs/Skills Tracking
- **Level input fields** with validation
- **Progress bars** showing current progress to next level
- **Job icons** for quick visual identification
- **Level-up celebrations** for milestone achievements

### Checklist Collections (Trusts, Mounts, etc.)
- **Checkbox interactions** with satisfying feedback
- **Completion percentages** prominently displayed
- **Filtering by obtained status**
- **Bulk actions** for mass updates

### Complex Collections (Quests, Missions)
- **Hierarchical organization** (expansion → area → quest)
- **Dependency visualization** showing prerequisites
- **Rich metadata** in expansion panels
- **Status tracking** with multiple states

## Performance Considerations

### Large Lists
- **Virtual scrolling** for 500+ items
- **Lazy loading** of images and metadata
- **Debounced search** to prevent excessive API calls
- **Efficient filtering** with client-side caching

### Data Updates
- **Optimistic updates** for immediate feedback
- **Conflict resolution** for concurrent edits
- **Auto-save** functionality with visual indicators
- **Offline support** with sync when reconnected

## Interaction Design

### Micro-Interactions
- **Satisfying completion** animations
- **Smooth transitions** between states
- **Tactile feedback** for mobile interactions
- **Progress celebrations** for milestones
- **Subtle sound effects** (optional)

### Navigation Flow
- **Breadcrumb trails** for complex hierarchies
- **Back button** functionality
- **Deep linking** to specific collections/items
- **Search result navigation**
- **Contextual actions** based on current view
